      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "The foundation's impact is rooted in its evidence-based approach to digital pedagogy. Data from their pilot programs indicates that students using their digital models achieved <cite id=\"10\">43% English alphabet writing proficiency</cite>, nearly four times the rate of the 11% found in control groups. This effectiveness is coupled with strong organizational transparency, as evidenced by their <cite id=\"11\">Gold Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite> and an <cite id=\"12\">overall score of 84.0/100 from Charity Navigator</cite>."
      ],
      "summary": "Teach-the-World Foundation Inc (TTWF) is a technology-driven non-profit founded in <cite id=\"1\">2016</cite> with the mission to eradicate global illiteracy through scalable digital learning models. The organization focuses on <cite id=\"2\">Malawi, Bangladesh, and Pakistan</cite>, deploying three primary delivery channels: <cite id=\"3\">Microschools, InSchool programs, and AtHome learning</cite>. By leveraging digital tablets and self-learning software, TTWF bypasses traditional infrastructure barriers to reach children in underserved regions. In the 2023 fiscal year, the foundation reported <cite id=\"4\">total revenue of $254,278</cite>, maintaining a lean operation that prioritizes direct educational delivery. Their model has demonstrated significant pedagogical success; for example, a Nielsen proof-of-concept study showed that students in the program achieved <cite id=\"5\">95% English alphabet recitation</cite> compared to only 58% in control groups. Furthermore, the foundation maintains <cite id=\"6\">a 100% independent board</cite>, ensuring high levels of governance and oversight for its international operations.",
